JOHANNESBURG - The editor of Huffington Post South Africa, Verashni Pillay, resigned at the weekend after the press ombudsman ruled that the contents of a blog published on the site amounted to hate speech.The article called for white men to be denied the right to vote.eNCA anchor Joanne Joseph hosted a debate on the issue.The participants were one of the complainants, AfriForums's Ernst Roets, head of policy at Media Monitoring Africa Thandi Smith and Freedom of Expression activist Sekoetlane Phamodi.* Watch the entire debate in the video above.eNCA